text: Ignacio Rodríguez (born 1999 in Montevideo) is an Uruguayan programmer, two- time winner of worldwide programming competition Google Code-in (in 2013 and in 2014) and a member of the Sugar Labs educational open-source organization. Rodríguez lives in Canelones. == References == Category:1999 births Category:Living people Category:One Laptop per Child Category:Free software programmers
